Silicon Valley Map & Calendar is a powerful branding tool that supports Northern California’s High Tech industry; while promoting regional, national, and global brands. Participants range from companies developing their first products to Fortune 100 multinationals.

Over 75,000 prints are published annually and distributed to industry professionals worldwide, at all levels, through trade shows, direct mail and by participating companies. The synergistic poster (Map, Calendar, and Custom Imprint) offers a high quality branding gift while creating a powerful Marketing, Sales, Communications, and HR tool.

The colorful posters are proudly displayed in executive offices, conference rooms, and work areas all year and viewed many times. The audience you care about will proudly display the poster and “Keep your brand visible all year!” Put Your Company on The Map!

Promotion Effectiveness
Participate in the High-Technology industry promotion surrounding the SILICON VALLEY Map. The popular industry poster features over 200 high tech innovators: most of the world’s top 20 technology companies as well as numerous emerging and midsize firms. Create brand awareness and support your location(s) while promoting your company as an industry leader. Over 100,000 copies are published annually. The Map/Calendar is displayed worldwide; find it in executive offices, lobbies, board rooms, cubicles, lunch rooms, conference rooms, elevators and other public places. The posters have an 85% + display rate! The creative design of the posters provides promotional effectiveness that ensures your message inculcates with your target audience, all year long! The Map/Calendar promotional posters are elegantly and professionally designed to enhance your brand.

Distribution targets entrepreneurial companies developing a first product to fortune 500 multinationals. Sponsors distribute copies to their target audience, internally and externally, worldwide.

Internally, companies distribute amongst Sales, Marketing, Public Affairs, Corporate Communications, Human Resources, executives and other company employees.

Externally, the promotional posters are distributed to stakeholders and constituents, including: CEO’s, Presidents, Vice Presidents, Manufacturers and Marketers, Business Development and Licensing Executives, Venture Capitalists and Entrepreneurs, Academic Researchers, Government Representatives, Industry Vendors, C-Levels & Business Executives, Bioscience & Healthcare Business Executives, University & Commercialization Leaders, Economic Development Executives, Trade Association Executives, etc.
